  "prompt": "Do the Lynda.com app movies have DRM?",
  "response": "Yes, Lynda.com (now part of LinkedIn Learning) typically provides its video content with Digital Rights Management (DRM) protection. This means that the videos may have restrictions on downloading and sharing to ensure that the content is used in compliance with the service's terms and conditions. If you're accessing content through their app, you may find that offline viewing is permitted for certain titles, but those downloads are often tied to your account and cannot be shared or played outside the app.",
